# Struxient v5 architecture

Pre-launch construction workflow app. Core promise: **know what is happening on a job and tell the right person what should happen next.**

## Before coding

1. Read relevant [`docs/canon/`](../../docs/canon/README.md) for product intent.
2. Read [`docs/architecture-guardrails.md`](../../docs/architecture-guardrails.md) and [`docs/source-of-truth-map.md`](../../docs/source-of-truth-map.md) for code locations.
3. Do **not** change `apps/web/prisma/schema.prisma` without explicit user approval (see `no-schema-without-approval.mdc`).

## Stored vs derived

- **Stored:** workflow facts — statuses, completion timestamps, issue/payment/recovery enums, activity rows.
- **Derived:** readiness, attention, blocking labels, commercial progress — compute via canonical helpers in `apps/web/src/lib/`.

Never add schema columns for values that should be derived.

## Domain spine

Lead → Quote (working commercial) → Checkpoints (hidden proof) → Job (runtime execution) → Activity (explanation).

Copy-on-activate: post-activation quote edits must not mutate materialized job rows.

## Where logic lives

| Domain | Canonical location |
|--------|-------------------|
| Task readiness | `lib/task-readiness.ts` |
| Payments due / holds | `lib/job-payment-readiness.ts` |
| Workstation queue | `lib/workstation-query.ts` |
| Issue resolve + recovery | `lib/resolve-job-issue-core.ts` |
| Quote / lead progress | `lib/quote-readiness.ts`, `lib/lead-commercial-progress.ts` |
| Server mutations | `app/**/**-actions.ts` scoped by `organizationId` |

## Work surfaces

Reuse `components/work-surfaces/*` and `components/jobs/task-work-surface.tsx`. Do not build parallel editors per route.

## Workstation

Attention cockpit only — see [`docs/workstation-guardrails.md`](../../docs/workstation-guardrails.md) and [workstation-canon.md](../../docs/canon/workstation-canon.md).

## AI

Proposals are **review-then-apply**. No silent persistence from AI output.

## Navigation — no breadcrumbs

**Never add breadcrumbs.** If a screen needs a trail to be understandable, the IA is too deep. Use sidebar, module subnav, `PageHeader` title, and `PageBackLink` for deep pages only. Canon: [workspace-ux-canon.md](../../docs/canon/workspace-ux-canon.md) §No breadcrumbs. Guardrail: `detect-breadcrumbs.mjs`.

